        <Document ID="3631BA94-F8F6-4181-AA30-A7A8BD291C74">
            <Title>Description</Title>
            <Text>Bloodletting is the first case in Investigation Technocraft.
A body is found tied up in a sex chair in the sex dungeon, Carnation Somatic, its extremities sliced down, his organs hanging out, motifs of the wraps of the chair show themselves in his hanging organs. This is the body of Curtis Wrecht, a man from Tin Town, and one of the close patrons of Elsbeth Anchlor, one of the most loved Dominatrixes in Tin Town.
Elsbeth is actually the one who approached Carpal PI for help with this case, she knows that if she went to the police she’d be automatically blamed because they wouldn’t put time into the actual investigation, instead trying to find an easy target to blame. If Carpal PI can prove that it wasn’t her, it will officially clear her name under the government of Technocraft city.
There are three people that could be the murderer, three people that had access to the room that Curtis Wrecht was murdered in: Elsbeth Anchlor, Vivienne Donohue, Zeke Skadinsky.



CONCEPT: The murderer wants to bloodlet the victim, relieve them of their sin, through leeches, the aesthetics of leeches.</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="1A345F36-9259-4770-8279-FD2F877A5B2D">
            <Title>Profile: Bianca Telluride</Title>
            <Text>Name: Bianca Telluride
Hobbies: Hacking, gardening, caretaking animals(specifically the concept of rabbits/bunnies… in this future there are no animals but people are fighting constantly to remind the rest of the world they used to exist and that humans like… got rid of them), fighting games, rhythm games, any twich-timing shit, smoking tobacco,  moderating forums
From: The suburbs of Technocraft city, the tristate area (this could probably have a name… maybe a small town on the coast that’s sort of revolving around high-profile workers in big businesses, similar to the energy of big pharma in new jersey?)
Religion:  a descendent of contemporary hinduism, he engages in the cultural practices but has weird feelings about religion… maybe he warships the “cyber god…” we’ll get there eventually
Gender: man, genderfluid, any pronouns, most people don’t know how to approach bianca’s gender and default to “he”
Height: 6’3
Hair: dark black, sort of like Dale Cooper’s when his hair does That
Build: muscular, strong, while sort of feminine for a male build (busty? Does that apply?), can tower but can also be demure, depends if he’s sitting or standing and on who he’s with, what he’s wearing.
Visual Description: Bianca keeps a light stubble along his jaw and the threat of a mustache above his upper lip, enough to stroke, enough to intimidate, not enough to scream of masc. Usually draped upon his broad shoulders is his leather trenchcoat, an heirloom from days before, passed down. It’s embossed with little intricate patterns that are common in his family’s culture. He likes to wear skirts that rise above his knee. In Technocraft, fashion like this is a little domineering towards people who are “conventional,” but most can’t recognize one another on the street anyway, in terms of gender or other forms of presentation, so when Bianca is around people, who are usually friendly with him, he gets few comments other than, “oh, that’s a pretty skirt!” His skirts would probably be like pleated but made from silk or something. I’d want him to wear black leggings or tights underneath, just because I feel like having skin exposed in Technocraft is dangerous in terms of like “the gasses seeping in” or something along those lines. He’d probably wear a turtleneck or something elegant like that under his long jacket, maybe a reddish-purple one.
Desc list: flakey, reliable, lustrous, elegant, pointed, impatient, intelligent, theatrical, masculine, arete, mysterious, intense
Mask: part purple, part blueish-green. the purple part is reminiscent of a motherboard of a computer and the blueish-green part is sort of similar to the scales of a lizard or the feathers of a peacock. Think the phantom of the opera mask, where the part that exists is like the peacock/lizard part and the part that doesn’t is the purple motherboard part.</Text>
